Type: Package
Package: validateHOT
Title: validateHOT - An R Package to validate holdout tasks and run market simulations 
Version: 1.0.4
Authors@R: c(person("Joshua", "Schramm", email = "joshua.schramm@mail.de", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-5602-4632")),
    person("Marcel", "Lichers", role = "ctb",
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-3710-2292"))
    )
Description: validateHOT is a package with three main objectives, (1) validates 
    validation (also called holdout tasks) in (adaptive) Conjoint analysis as well as
    MaxDiff, (2) perform market simulations, and (3) convert raw utilities into 
    scores that are easier to interpret and report.
    validateHOT is a user-friendly tool to help you test the predictive validity
    of your data and run relevant marketing simulations with utilities obtained
    through a Hierarchical Bayes estimation (or mixed logit). 
    validateHOT works best with data obtained through Hierarchical Bayesian 
    estimation with Sawtooth Software or ChoiceModelR.
